{[#]} {[%tqu "En","White to move.","","","c4e6","I think this is the only viable approach to fight for an advantage. I played this move myself in 2 games against strong GMs.",10,"c2c3","was played in the game Yoo-Aronina, USA-ch Saint Louis 2022.",0,"f1d1","This move doesn't come with tempo now.",0]} 8. Bxe6 $5 {I think this is the only viable approach to fight for an advantage. I played this move myself in 2 games against strong GMs.} (8. c3 {was played in the game Yoo-Aronina, USA-ch Saint Louis 2022.} d5 $1 $11 {[%csl Bd5] GM Aronian was well prepared, and showed the best path to equality:}) (8. Rd1 $6 {[%csl Gd4,Ge6] This move doesn't come with tempo now.} d5 $1 $36 {Logical move, and probably Black is the one fighting for the advantage.}) 8... dxe6 9. Rd1 Be7 10. Nc3 $1 $36 {[%csl Bc3][%cal Gc3b5] Key move to remember, since the pawn can be recaptured in many ways, but this is the most precise.} *

